President Donald J. Trump has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the Inaugural Ceremonies of President-Elect George Weah in Monrovia, Liberia on January 22, 2018. The United States is proud to celebrate Liberia's first peaceful transfer of power in decades, which is seen as a major milestone for the country's democracy and for Africa as a whole. The delegation will be led by Under Secretary for Political Affairs, Thomas A. Shannon Jr., and includes the United States Ambassador to Liberia, Christine A. Elder, Senior Director for African Affairs, Cyril E. Sartor, The Adjutant General of the Michigan National Guard, Major General Gregory J. Vadnais, and Deputy Assistant Secretary, Stephanie S. Sullivan. This delegation highlights the importance of the partnership between the United States and Africa and the commitment to Africa's growth and success.